Netflix has announced the Netflix Gift Card, which will provide another way of paying for their services. Set to be released this month, these gift cards can be loaded with between R150 to R1,000 and will not expire. Existing Netflix members can use the gift card to top up their Netflix account credit, while those who don’t yet have an account can redeem their credit by visiting netflix.com/redeem. Fans who have not subscribed to Netflix because they don’t have – or don’t want to link – a credit card can use these gift cards as a long-term, secure payment method. New subscribers who are eligible for a free trial will receive a free month of service in addition to the amount credited to the gift card. These gift cards will be available from a variety of retailers, including: